ITEMS.ASH.5.12.97

This document describes some of the quality control expectations. 

Short descriptions:
           a. always use lowercase for every word.
           b. refrain from using "a" or "an" to start a description.
           c. every short description should have atleast 2 adjectives.   
           c. Example: set_short("fancy black cape");

Long descriptions:
           a. Proper capitalization and punctation required, for muds
              this means only 1 space after periods.
           b. the shortest long description should be 2 FULL lines.
              the average long description for an item will be 3 or
              more lines, please dont make descriptions longer then
              6 lines unless it is extremly special.
           e. avoid ALL use of third person speech when creating a
              item description.
           f. AVOID 'A SuPeR cOOl Shield', etc.
          
The following aditional functions must be defined.
           a. set_name   (MUST BE ONLY ONE WORD)
           b. set_weight (see /doc/mudlib/balance + /doc/mudlib/weight)
           c. set_value  (see /doc/mudlib/balance + /doc/mudlib/value)
           d. set_ac [armours only] (see /doc/mudlib/balance)
           e. set_wc [weapons only] (see /doc/mudlib/balance)
 
Please use /doc/mudlib/balance document to balance items.

Please, if you wish to comment upon any of this, feel VERY free to mail Admin.

